Magistrate Vernon Jantjies was gunned down at a filling station in Lentegeur, Cape Town. CAPE TOWN - A magistrate was shot and killed in Mitchells Plain on Sunday night. Magistrate Vernon Jantjies was gunned down at a filling station in Lentegeur, Cape Town. The local community policing forum’s Byron de Villiers said: “It certainly looks like they targeted him and no suspects have been identified yet.” No arrests have been made.